STATE
v.
Jeral Thomas ORE, Jr. 352P16-1 Supreme Court of North Carolina. March 16, 2017 Kimberly P. Hoppin, Attorney at Law, for Ore, Jeral Thomas (Jr.). M. Elizabeth Guzman, Assistant Attorney General, Roger A. Echols, District Attorney, for State of North Carolina.

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 26th of September 2016 by State of NC for Temporary Stay:

"Motion Dissolved by order of the Court in conference, this the 16th of March 2017."
